          "email": "bruno.faccini@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-06-19 18:26:47.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "SGI-133 mdt: remove cdt_llog_lock mutex",
        "message": "SGI-133 mdt: remove cdt_llog_lock mutex\n\nDuring early HSM development, issues had been encountered\nwhen using LLOG layer during concurrent hsm_actions usage.\nTo avoid this, cdt_llog_lock mutex defensive protection had\nbeen introduced to serialize hsm_actions LLOG usages.\nAs LLOG layer has been reworked and is guaranteed to be\nthread-safe, this protection use is no longer required.\nThis may help to have CDT's performance better scale when\nhandling thousands of requests.\n\nAdditional change has been to rewrite all hsm_actions record\nupdate cases to switch from non-atomical \"add new, then\nremove old\" current way to an in-place update of existing record.\n\nTest-Parameters: envdefinitions=PTLDEBUG=-1,DEBUG_SIZE=1024\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iaf763a575f953a058e2cfbdfc84e12e6ed0c9059\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
